# docker-Mopidy-Linux.
Let Mopidy run in a docker container.
[Mopidy](https://mopidy.com/) is an extensible music server written in Python.
It can be build for Linux AMD64 and Rpi RaspiOS armv architecture.

Used by multiroom sound system running under ProjectAlice.

It's a companion app to skill MultiRomMpdManager.



Read [Requirements](#Requirements), [Installing](#Installing)


## Installing.
set the environment in the file Timezone.env:
   TZ=Area/Location
   e.g. TZ=Europe/Copenhagen

Be sure to build it with "bash build.sh" With "bash build.sh" you get the right UID and GID in the container and the rigth setup.


## Requirements.
[Docker](https://www.docker.com/) installed.

- `sudo curl -fsSL get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh && sh get-docker.sh`

How to set up Docker to run without using sudo all the time.

 - `sudo usermod -aG docker $USER`

Log out and log in again to access the docker group.

Install of docker-compose:
-  sudo apt install -y libffi-dev \
  python3-venv python3-pip \
  && sudo pip3 install docker-compose

